-- Turquoise Resumes Trading After Network Error Delays Opening on Second Day
-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 2010-10-05T08:35:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/turquoise-resumes-trading-after-network-error-delays-opening-on-second-day.html
London Stock Exchange Group Plc
resumed trading on its Turquoise platform at 9:15 a.m. in
London, after a network error forced the exchange to delay the
opening of the market.  “We think it was an internal network error overnight,”
Alastair Fairbrother, a spokesman for LSE, said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  